      "rdfs:comment": [
        "DEFINITION: An obligation that is not yet firm. There is some contingent event whose occurrence will cause the obligation to become firm.",
        "NOTE: A contingent obligation might have a getter counterparty (as in the case of insurance); but it might not (as in the case of an offer)."
      ],
